{"info":{"name":"jartexBotExtension","description":"Custom plugin loaded into every bot for this server.","editedAt":1779742337361,"uploadedAt":null,"createdAt":1779736439134,"public":false,"type":"private","language":"js","scriptType":"botExtension","flags":0,"downloads":0,"theme":{"primaryColor":"#2193b0","secondaryColor":"#6dd5ed","accentColor":"#2193b0","gradientStart":"#2193b0","gradientEnd":"#6dd5ed","tagColor":"#6dd5ed"},"settings":{},"pluginId":"mpll4h994wctko2srpn","folder":"JartexProfile"},"code":{"code":"// Bot extension — runs once per bot instance, loaded as the LAST\n// mineflayer plugin for this server. Use it to override built-in bot\n// methods, attach event listeners, or expose new APIs on the bot.\n//\n// The exported function is called by mineflayer as a plugin:\n//   inject(bot, options)\n//\n// You have full access to the bot instance and may mutate it.\n\nconst {\n  nbtToStr,\n} = require('jnbotNbt');\nconst regex = /([0-9]+ms|\u001b|You are connected to )|Playing at |§./g;\n\n\nfunction inject(bot) {\n  // ---- Example 1: log every chat message --------------------------------\n  // bot.on('messagestr', (msg) => console.log('[chat]', msg));\n\n  // ---- Example 2: wrap an existing method -------------------------------\n  // const originalJoin = bot.join?.bind(bot);\n  // if (originalJoin) {\n  //   bot.join = async (gamemode, options) => {\n  //     console.log('joining', gamemode);\n  //     return originalJoin(gamemode, options);\n  //   };\n  // }\n\n  // ---- Example 3: add a custom helper -----------------------------------\n  // bot.sayHi = () => bot.chat('hi from my extension!');\n\n  bot.getGamemode = () => {\n    let gm = bot.scoreboard.sidebar?.title;\n    if (typeof gm === 'object' && gm.value) {\n      gm = nbtToStr(gm);\n    }\n\n    gm = gm?.replace?.(regex, '')?.toAlpha();\n    if (gm && gm.trim().length > 0 && gm.trim().charCodeAt(0) <= 128) {\n      return gm;\n    }\n\n    return bot.tablist.header\n      ?.toString()\n      ?.trim()\n      ?.split('\\n')[1]\n      ?.replace(regex, '')\n      .toAlpha()\n      .trim();\n  };\n\n\n  bot.getNextGkitPageSlot = () => {\n    if (!bot.currentWindow) return -1;\n\n    let lastSlot = bot.currentWindow.inventoryStart;\n    for (let i = lastSlot - 9; i < lastSlot; i++) {\n      const slot = bot.currentWindow.slots[i];\n      if (slot && bot.itemInfo(slot).name.toLowerCase().includes('next page')) {\n        return i;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // In OPfactions, the next page button is an arrow at position 35 | 26, let's check for that as well\n\n    const arrowSlot = bot.currentWindow.slots[35] ? 35 : 26;\n    const nextPageSlot = bot.currentWindow.slots[arrowSlot];\n    if (nextPageSlot && nextPageSlot.name === 'arrow') {\n      return arrowSlot;\n    }\n\n    return -1;\n  }\n\n}\n\nmodule.exports = inject;\n"},"signature":""}